        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:45PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms
around Trinity, or 17 miles northeast of Huntsville, moving east at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northeastern Huntsville, Apple Springs, Trinity, Onalaska, Corrigan,
Groveton, Point Blank, Riverside, Seven Oaks, Sebastopol, Moscow, and
Oakhurst.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
